If you play a full year of tournaments,

7
00:01:51,680 --> 00:01:53,520
you could earn over a hundred million.

8
00:01:53,680 --> 00:01:54,910
We split it ninety to ten.

9
00:01:55,400 --> 00:01:58,040
Thanks, but pro Go isn't for me.

10
00:01:59,000 --> 00:02:00,310
I get one, you get nine.

11
00:02:01,840 --> 00:02:03,150
It's not about the money.

12
00:02:03,950 --> 00:02:05,310
With your talent,

13
00:02:05,310 --> 00:02:07,110
it's a shame to let it go to waste.

14
00:02:07,110 --> 00:02:08,400
It'd be such a loss.

15
00:02:10,910 --> 00:02:13,270
I know a top former national player.

16
00:02:13,270 --> 00:02:14,560
He's looking for a student now.

17
00:02:14,560 --> 00:02:15,950
Want me to introduce you?

18
00:02:18,270 --> 00:02:19,270
He already has a teacher.

19
00:02:19,910 --> 00:02:20,950
You should answer your phone first.

20
00:02:21,360 --> 00:02:22,430
Seems pretty urgent.

21
00:02:26,680 --> 00:02:27,400
About what I told you,

22
00:02:27,400 --> 00:02:28,430
think it over carefully.

23
00:02:29,040 --> 00:02:29,950
Take your time with it.

24
00:02:33,880 --> 00:02:35,430
Ying can be pretty direct.

25
00:02:35,720 --> 00:02:36,720
Don't take it to heart.

26
00:02:36,880 --> 00:02:37,680
It's okay.

27
00:02:40,080 --> 00:02:41,950
I haven't

28
00:02:41,950 --> 00:02:42,630
thanked you yet.

29
00:02:43,360 --> 00:02:44,720
As long as I didn't slow you down.

30
00:02:47,790 --> 00:02:50,000
Are you free this afternoon?

31
00:02:51,360 --> 00:02:52,680
I've got plans later.

32
00:02:54,630 --> 00:02:55,790
Do you need something?

33
00:02:57,630 --> 00:02:58,790
It's nothing major.

34
00:02:59,270 --> 00:03:00,310
Well,

35
00:03:00,310 --> 00:03:03,080
I still owe you a thank-you gift.

36
00:03:03,560 --> 00:03:06,240
I figured a book would be best,

37
00:03:06,360 --> 00:03:08,360
and I thought
you could pick one yourself.

38
00:03:09,400 --> 00:03:10,310
Thank you, Ms. Jiang.

39
00:03:11,430 --> 00:03:13,560
I actually need to buy books
in Hang City.

40
00:03:14,110 --> 00:03:15,520
I'll send you the address then.

41
00:03:16,400 --> 00:03:18,840
Have you decided to head to Hang City?

42
00:03:19,790 --> 00:03:21,270
Thanks to Mr. Jiang's recommendation letter,

43
00:03:21,590 --> 00:03:23,680
I got an interview at Risheng.

44
00:03:25,000 --> 00:03:26,910
I should be leaving
in a couple of days.

45
00:03:29,520 --> 00:03:31,000
You're only in your twenties.

46
00:03:31,430 --> 00:03:33,270
This is such a crucial time
in your life.

47
00:03:35,720 --> 00:03:39,000
Finance might not be what you expect.

48
00:03:39,950 --> 00:03:41,400
It can get pretty dull.

49
00:03:41,750 --> 00:03:43,200
It can gradually make you rigid.

50
00:03:46,520 --> 00:03:47,840
That doesn't sound like

51
00:03:48,680 --> 00:03:51,000
an English teacher talking.

52
00:03:53,240 --> 00:03:54,950
Throughout one's life,

53
00:03:54,950 --> 00:03:56,150
who decides what's important,

54
00:03:56,270 --> 00:03:57,880
and what's not, anyway?

55
00:03:58,880 --> 00:04:00,470
We all end up the same in the end.

56
00:04:01,000 --> 00:04:02,400
So just do what you want.

57
00:04:02,790 --> 00:04:04,630
It's never the world that's rigid.

58
00:04:05,110 --> 00:04:06,080
It's our minds.

59
00:04:07,270 --> 00:04:09,590
Some people can only find peace
in the mountains,

60
00:04:09,880 --> 00:04:11,910
while others find calm
in the city chaos.

61
00:04:12,110 --> 00:04:13,000
It's the same idea.

62
00:04:28,240 --> 00:04:29,720
Can I run something by you?

63
00:04:30,750 --> 00:04:31,560
Go ahead.

64
00:04:31,720 --> 00:04:33,560
We're friends now, right?

65
00:04:34,240 --> 00:04:35,720
So, stop calling me "miss".

66
00:04:36,630 --> 00:04:37,430
No problem.

67
00:04:54,080 --> 00:04:55,560
Is she your girlfriend?

68
00:04:55,560 --> 00:04:56,360
No, she's not.

69
00:04:56,520 --> 00:04:58,400
We're just online friends.

70
00:04:59,520 --> 00:05:02,000
We met in a finance group years ago.

71
00:05:33,560 --> 00:05:37,560
"Where can I gaze upon the Divine Land?

72
00:05:38,520 --> 00:05:44,110
Panoramic views from

73
00:05:44,750 --> 00:05:46,720
Beigu Tower unfold.

74
00:05:46,720 --> 00:05:50,000
Rise and fall through ages grand...

75
00:05:57,240 --> 00:06:00,310
Sun Quan led ten-thousand men at youth....

76
00:06:00,310 --> 00:06:02,270
an army of ten-thousand men..."

77
00:06:19,790 --> 00:06:21,360
"Sun Quan led an army of
ten-thousand men at youth.

78
00:06:22,880 --> 00:06:26,400
Firmly holding the Southeast,
warfare never ceased."

79
00:06:28,520 --> 00:06:30,310
I finally learned how to say "army".

80
00:06:31,200 --> 00:06:34,430
But you'll never be a hero.

81
00:06:34,430 --> 00:06:36,160
[My beloved father, Wei Mingyi]

82
00:06:37,080 --> 00:06:38,040
You left without looking back,

83
00:06:38,040 --> 00:06:39,040
pretty decisive.

84
00:06:41,150 --> 00:06:42,750
But you left a mess behind for me.

85
00:06:44,680 --> 00:06:47,080
I had no choice
but to stay with the Lis.

86
00:06:48,750 --> 00:06:50,750
Now I have to come visit you
every month,

87
00:06:53,360 --> 00:06:55,110
just to show Li Minxian I care.

88
00:07:07,680 --> 00:07:08,560
He has been...

89
00:07:09,680 --> 00:07:11,470
putting on more airs lately.

90
00:07:13,200 --> 00:07:15,950
Thinking back,
the Li family's first pot of gold

91
00:07:18,840 --> 00:07:20,400
was all thanks to your help.

92
00:07:22,430 --> 00:07:23,470
But in the end,

93
00:07:24,910 --> 00:07:26,080
it all came to nothing.

94
00:07:28,080 --> 00:07:28,910
They've made it big now,

95
00:07:31,470 --> 00:07:32,950
but all you got is one comment.

96
00:07:34,950 --> 00:07:36,270
You were a good guy.

97
00:07:39,110 --> 00:07:40,590
But from this matter,

98
00:07:41,910 --> 00:07:43,240
I've learned something important.

99
00:07:45,430 --> 00:07:46,240
People

100
00:07:47,080 --> 00:07:48,430
either get used by money

101
00:07:49,520 --> 00:07:51,000
or by affections.

102
00:07:52,430 --> 00:07:54,910
If you're the first to show your heart,

103
00:07:57,470 --> 00:07:59,110
you'll end up as just a pawn.

104
00:08:03,750 --> 00:08:04,680
I'm alive

105
00:08:08,790 --> 00:08:09,880
just to win.

106
00:08:11,560 --> 00:08:13,630
I'll get everything

107
00:08:14,520 --> 00:08:16,270
they took from you back

108
00:08:17,200 --> 00:08:18,310
one by one.

109
00:08:22,150 --> 00:08:23,750
When it's finally all done,

110
00:08:24,430 --> 00:08:26,680
maybe I'll ask Zhao Xin for you,

111
00:08:27,910 --> 00:08:28,790
see if he still remembers

112
00:08:32,470 --> 00:08:33,680
who Wei Mingyi is.

113
00:08:50,750 --> 00:08:52,560
I'll come see you again next month.

114
00:08:52,950 --> 00:08:54,000
Coward Dad.

115
00:09:04,000 --> 00:09:05,840
I checked on what you asked me to do.

116
00:09:06,080 --> 00:09:07,310
It's just like you guessed.

117
00:09:09,110 --> 00:09:11,000
Wei Jinghai is the son of an old friend.

118
00:09:11,590 --> 00:09:13,080
Li Minxian raised him.

119
00:09:15,040 --> 00:09:16,750
I've known Wei Mingyi for years.

120
00:09:16,750 --> 00:09:18,240
I've never heard of

121
00:09:18,240 --> 00:09:20,110
him getting married and having a kid.

122
00:09:22,000 --> 00:09:23,880
If I hadn't seen that boy's eyes,

123
00:09:24,680 --> 00:09:26,470
I wouldn't even dare think about it.

124
00:09:27,080 --> 00:09:28,430
If I'd known it,

125
00:09:28,430 --> 00:09:30,000
I would've brought him back

126
00:09:30,000 --> 00:09:31,110
as I did to Dongcao.

127
00:09:31,360 --> 00:09:32,720
Dongcao knows what's right.

128
00:09:33,840 --> 00:09:35,080
She's got kindness in her heart.

129
00:09:35,110 --> 00:09:37,080
But not everyone is like her.

130
00:09:41,630 --> 00:09:43,430
After all these years in business,

131
00:09:44,080 --> 00:09:45,750
few people have moved me,

132
00:09:47,150 --> 00:09:48,400
but Wei Mingyi is one of them.

133
00:09:49,470 --> 00:09:51,360
Back when Mr. Qi was in trouble,

134
00:09:52,470 --> 00:09:53,310
I was left

135
00:09:53,310 --> 00:09:54,430
no other choice.

136
00:09:55,560 --> 00:09:56,880
Back then, I thought,

137
00:09:57,360 --> 00:09:58,910
after things settled down,

138
00:09:59,240 --> 00:10:02,880
I'd take everything I had and find him.

139
00:10:03,240 --> 00:10:04,360
But who could've thought...

140
00:10:10,310 --> 00:10:12,630
You've sent Fu Fang and the others
to the mining site.

141
00:10:12,750 --> 00:10:13,630
Can you really trust them?

142
00:10:15,590 --> 00:10:16,400
Uncle,

143
00:10:17,520 --> 00:10:19,790
I entered the mining site for business,

144
00:10:19,880 --> 00:10:21,360
not to stir up any fights.

145
00:10:22,630 --> 00:10:23,680
As long as that boy from the Wei family

146
00:10:24,880 --> 00:10:26,270
doesn't cross my line

147
00:10:26,360 --> 00:10:27,590
and cause trouble, it's fine.

148
00:10:29,310 --> 00:10:30,150
By the way, Uncle,

149
00:10:31,630 --> 00:10:33,310
that rascal

150
00:10:33,310 --> 00:10:34,270
went to Hang City.

151
00:10:36,430 --> 00:10:37,200
Yeah, I know.

152
00:10:40,680 --> 00:10:42,430
After raising eagles for years,

153
00:10:42,430 --> 00:10:43,790
I've realized something.

154
00:10:44,240 --> 00:10:45,750
Raising eagles is like raising people.

155
00:10:45,950 --> 00:10:47,200
Eagles need to be strong,

156
00:10:47,310 --> 00:10:48,430
but can't get too many muscles.

157
00:10:48,590 --> 00:10:49,560
As for raising people,

158
00:10:49,790 --> 00:10:51,310
you need to break their arrogance,

159
00:10:51,430 --> 00:10:53,560
but keep their pride.

160
00:10:56,200 --> 00:10:57,590
What do you think?

161
00:10:57,950 --> 00:10:59,430
I can pretty much guess it.

162
00:11:00,000 --> 00:11:02,840
But I wonder
if Baliang can handle it.

163
00:11:03,910 --> 00:11:06,880
After all, it's their turf.

164
00:11:07,310 --> 00:11:10,110
Plus, he's carrying your debt.

165
00:11:13,360 --> 00:11:15,000
When I first started out on my own,

166
00:11:15,590 --> 00:11:16,910
let me tell you,

167
00:11:17,360 --> 00:11:18,470
forget roughing it outdoors.

168
00:11:20,110 --> 00:11:22,080
Even if it's just scraps of food
someone else left,

169
00:11:22,840 --> 00:11:24,110
I'd kneel down

170
00:11:24,110 --> 00:11:26,520
and lick them clean, not leaving a bit.

171
00:11:28,150 --> 00:11:28,950
Uncle,

172
00:11:29,430 --> 00:11:30,840
compared to me,

173
00:11:31,750 --> 00:11:33,000
he knows nothing about hardship.

174
00:11:35,470 --> 00:11:36,950
You Zhaos

175
00:11:37,520 --> 00:11:40,400
are all stubborn as mules.

176
00:11:45,880 --> 00:11:48,590
Your biggest flaw

177
00:11:48,590 --> 00:11:50,310
is being way too proud.

178
00:11:50,790 --> 00:11:52,000
You win ninety-nine moves,

179
00:11:52,000 --> 00:11:52,950
but lose just one,

180
00:11:52,950 --> 00:11:54,720
and you lose the whole game.

181
00:11:59,200 --> 00:12:00,720
I actually feel for Baliang.

182
00:12:00,910 --> 00:12:02,310
Not because I'm afraid he'll struggle,

183
00:12:03,720 --> 00:12:06,110
but because he has
such a good foundation and nature,

184
00:12:06,310 --> 00:12:08,080
yet you keep forcing him
to grow too fast.

185
00:12:09,400 --> 00:12:10,910
Still, I'm kind of curious.

186
00:12:11,240 --> 00:12:12,520
Back then,

187
00:12:12,520 --> 00:12:14,630
you were set on expanding south,

188
00:12:14,680 --> 00:12:16,470
constantly clashing with Li Minxian,

189
00:12:16,630 --> 00:12:19,310
which ended up helping them
form a chamber of commerce.

190
00:12:19,360 --> 00:12:20,750
In the end, you got nothing.

191
00:12:22,310 --> 00:12:25,360
Now it's Jiadi,
who actually has compassion.

192
00:12:26,470 --> 00:12:27,270
Maybe...

193
00:12:29,150 --> 00:12:30,470
this is a new opportunity.

194
00:12:45,320 --> 00:12:46,720
Where the hell are you?

195
00:12:47,160 --> 00:12:49,880
If you don't get out soon,
we'll miss our stop.

196
00:12:59,000 --> 00:12:59,790
It's packed up front.

197
00:12:59,790 --> 00:13:00,790
I'm at the end of the train.

198
00:13:05,950 --> 00:13:09,720
Dear passengers,
we're arriving at Jia City Station.

199
00:13:10,080 --> 00:13:12,750
Please get ready to get off in advance,

200
00:13:13,200 --> 00:13:15,080
and make sure
you have all your belongings.

201
00:13:15,240 --> 00:13:17,110
Please don't leave them on board.

202
00:13:17,360 --> 00:13:19,790
We want to avoid any trouble for you.

203
00:13:20,560 --> 00:13:22,880
Looking forward to seeing you again.

204
00:13:23,520 --> 00:13:25,240
Have a pleasant journey.

205
00:13:27,470 --> 00:13:28,270
Excuse me, sir.

206
00:13:30,630 --> 00:13:31,840
Did you take the wrong bag?

207
00:13:35,590 --> 00:13:37,200
Are you sure that's your bag?

208
00:13:38,150 --> 00:13:38,750
It's mine.

209
00:13:38,750 --> 00:13:39,750
I know my own stuff.

210
00:13:39,750 --> 00:13:40,520
Mind your own business.

211
00:13:40,520 --> 00:13:41,200
Wait.

212
00:13:42,200 --> 00:13:43,430
Maybe open it to check.

213
00:13:43,590 --> 00:13:45,240
It'd be a hassle if it's not yours.

214
00:13:45,240 --> 00:13:46,000
What's wrong with you?

215
00:13:46,000 --> 00:13:46,950
I'm in a rush to get off.

216
00:13:46,950 --> 00:13:47,750
Let go of me.

217
00:13:47,750 --> 00:13:49,150
It's better if you check now.

218
00:13:49,360 --> 00:13:51,200
Let go, I'm getting off now.

219
00:13:52,470 --> 00:13:53,840
Sir,

220
00:13:54,310 --> 00:13:55,430
you got here just in time.

221
00:13:56,080 --> 00:13:56,880
What happened?

222
00:13:59,080 --> 00:14:01,080
Please, take it easy.

223
00:14:01,150 --> 00:14:02,630
Please put your hand down.

224
00:14:02,720 --> 00:14:03,400
Let's talk this out,

225
00:14:03,400 --> 00:14:04,000
okay?

226
00:14:04,000 --> 00:14:04,720
What's going on?

227
00:14:04,720 --> 00:14:05,880
When we got on earlier,

228
00:14:05,880 --> 00:14:07,110
didn't I help you put it up?

229
00:14:07,520 --> 00:14:09,110
There's another one just like it.

230
00:14:09,110 --> 00:14:10,310
Maybe this gentleman
took the wrong one.

231
00:14:10,310 --> 00:14:11,240
Please, check your bag.

232
00:14:11,470 --> 00:14:12,150
So... so,

233
00:14:12,150 --> 00:14:13,360
let's just have a check

234
00:14:13,360 --> 00:14:14,310
to avoid misunderstanding.

235
00:14:14,310 --> 00:14:15,750
Why do I have to check my bag?

236
00:14:16,000 --> 00:14:17,000
I'm in a hurry to get off.

237
00:14:17,000 --> 00:14:17,430
Hold on.

238
00:14:18,400 --> 00:14:19,360
Just open your bag.

239
00:14:19,360 --> 00:14:20,360
Let's take a quick look.

240
00:14:20,470 --> 00:14:21,430
Do you want a fight?

241
00:14:21,430 --> 00:14:22,430
Open it up and check inside.

242
00:14:22,430 --> 00:14:23,360
Let go!

243
00:14:23,360 --> 00:14:24,110
The gentleman asked you

244
00:14:24,110 --> 00:14:24,790
to open the bag.

245
00:14:24,790 --> 00:14:25,430
Let's have a look inside.

246
00:14:25,430 --> 00:14:26,520
Are you serious? Let go of me!

247
00:14:26,520 --> 00:14:27,400
I'll let go once you check it.

248
00:14:27,400 --> 00:14:28,910
Are you letting go or not?
If not, I won't be nice.

249
00:14:28,910 --> 00:14:29,790
No, I'm not letting go.

250
00:14:29,790 --> 00:14:31,000
Then I'll have to get physical.

251
00:14:31,040 --> 00:14:31,950
- Calm down.
- Let go!

252
00:14:32,360 --> 00:14:33,680
If you don't let go, I'll use force!

253
00:14:33,680 --> 00:14:34,470
What's happening here?

254
00:14:35,470 --> 00:14:36,310
Officers.

255
00:14:38,520 --> 00:14:40,040
What's going on?

256
00:14:40,520 --> 00:14:41,470
Here's the situation.

257
00:14:41,790 --> 00:14:43,590
When this gentleman boarded,

258
00:14:43,590 --> 00:14:45,470
I helped put his bag up.

259
00:14:46,080 --> 00:14:47,880
There was a cartoon print under his bag.

260
00:14:48,040 --> 00:14:49,790
I think he might have the wrong bag.

261
00:14:50,310 --> 00:14:51,110
Officer,

262
00:14:51,110 --> 00:14:52,110
I'm in a rush to get off.

263
00:14:52,110 --> 00:14:53,470
He won't let me leave.

264
00:14:53,790 --> 00:14:54,790
Please cooperate with me.

265
00:14:54,910 --> 00:14:56,000
Let me check your bag.

266
00:14:56,310 --> 00:14:57,470
It's just my bag, nothing special.

267
00:14:57,470 --> 00:14:58,520
It's fine, just a quick check.

268
00:15:04,750 --> 00:15:06,080
That's my granddaughter's toy.

269
00:15:06,080 --> 00:15:08,240
No idea when she stuck it on.

270
00:15:08,400 --> 00:15:09,630
This is my bag.

271
00:15:09,630 --> 00:15:10,880
- This is my bag.
- Alright.

272
00:15:11,310 --> 00:15:12,280
So this one's yours.

273
00:15:13,350 --> 00:15:14,190
Where's your bag then?

274
00:15:15,040 --> 00:15:15,760
My bag?

275
00:15:17,920 --> 00:15:18,920
Maybe this is actually mine.

276
00:15:19,790 --> 00:15:20,560
They look the same.

277
00:15:20,600 --> 00:15:21,470
It was a mix-up.

278
00:15:21,560 --> 00:15:22,560
Sorry about that.

279
00:15:22,790 --> 00:15:23,280
I'm sorry.

280
00:15:23,280 --> 00:15:25,510
